GRAEME McDOWELL:   Yeah, team golf is always something that I've loved.   My three Ryder Cups have been my best golfing experiences of my career so far, and you know, golf's such an individual sport, I think any time you get to sit in the team room and bond with some great players, partner up in better‑balls and foursomes golf and play for each other, I think it's something I love.   When I had the opportunity to come here and play in this event, I certainly jumped at the chance.   I felt an opportunity to really whet the appetite for The Ryder Cup later in the season, which we are all trying to get on that team.   I thought this week would be a really great experience.   First time back in Malaysia in a few years.   We have a great team this week and I think we can do a good job for our captain here.   
   
