 Q.   Is the course for long hitters?   
VICTOR DUBUISSON:   You said the course is not meant for a long hitter?   No, I played this morning, it's a great course.   You still have to hit the ball long.   It's a good advantage on the par 5s if you hit the ball long, but no, the more important is to hit it on the fairway, so it's the same.   
   
 Q.   A couple of players on the Asian team, team Asia, they play regularly on The European Tour and a lot of others are hoping to get on to The European Tour in the coming years; any thoughts on them, how you have seen them over the past few years?   
MIGUEL ANGEL JIMÃNEZ:   Well, I thought that the Asian game, as I said before in previous interviews‑‑ the golf now is very healthy in all the world, in all the continents.   The golf is growing and the players, there are very good players all over the place.   As you see, they are coming here in Europe and they are coming to America to play, and in Japan, all over the place.   It's not much different like 20 years ago.   Now I think the level is very similar all over the place and you have great players around here, too.   
Regarding this week, they are going to be interesting matches, yeah.   
   
 Q.   What are your hopes for the future in terms of this tournament?   
MIGUEL ANGEL JIMÃNEZ:   The hopes for the tournament?   For the future?   Well, I remember‑‑ well, I don't remember because I haven't been born yet, but The Ryder Cup started in 1927 and probably now is the event in golf and everyone wants to play I think is the main thing.   And now we start the EurAsia Cup in 2014 and the EurAsia Cup, it needs to be with all the players and everything, some time is something very nice.   I think with the effort of these two big tours and the effort of the players, the EurAsia Cup will become a big event and also important with the majors.   
   
